title: ICE: debug assertions: E0061: `suggestion must not have overlapping parts`

labels.name: A-diagnostics
labels.description: Area: Messages for errors, warnings, and lints

labels.name: I-ICE
labels.description: Issue: The compiler panicked, giving an Internal Compilation Error (ICE) ❄️

labels.name: T-compiler
labels.description: Relevant to the compiler team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue.

labels.name: requires-debug-assertions
labels.description: This issue requires debug-assertions in some way

body:
### Code You need rustc built with debug assertions in order to reproduce this! ```Rust struct A; struct B; fn f(b1: B, b2: B, a2: C) {} fn main() { f(A, A, B, C); } ``` ### Meta `rustc --version --verbose`: ``` b9535c0b7d64290b27c4a116262402cd12f77833 ``` ### Error output ``` error[E0061]: this function takes 3 arguments but 4 arguments were supplied --> treereduce.out:7:5 | 7 | f(A, A, B, C); | ^ - - - unexpected argument | | | | | expected `B`, found `A` | expected `B`, found `A` | note: function defined here --> treereduce.out:4:4 | 4 | fn f(b1: B, b2: B, a2: C) {} | ^ ----- ----- ----- help: remove the extra argument | 7 - f(A, A, B, C); 7 + f(/* B *//* B */, A, B); | ```
